Detailed Description

Options for the disasembly formatting functions. Set once during initialization by a calling xed_format_set_options

unsigned int xed_format_options_t::hex_address_before_symbolic_name

by default, XED prints the hex address before any symbolic name for branch targets. If set to zero, then XED will not print the hex address before a valid symbolic name.
